Charles Henry Gausden (1826 – 5 September 1886) was an English cricketer.  Gausden's batting style is unknown.  He was born at Brasted, Kent.
Gausden made his first-class debut for Sussex against the Marylebone Cricket Club in 1847.  He made four further first-class appearances for the county, the last of which came against the Marylebone Cricket Club in 1851.  In his five first-class matches, he scored 41 runs at an average of 5.85, with a high score of 17.He died at St Leonards-on-Sea, Sussex in 1886.
